      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "John Stuart Mill's harm principle is a powerful tool here; the state should only intervene when speech directly causes demonstrable harm, not merely because it is unpopular or disagreeable. Modern libertarianism builds on this by viewing the internet as the ultimate \"marketplace of ideas,\" where the free exchange of all viewpoints, even offensive ones, is necessary for truth to emerge. Government regulation inevitably stifles dissenting or challenging voices, thereby corrupting the very mechanism by which society discovers truth.",
